{"type":"message","id":"70755a2d","parentId":"3cb509d5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:20:38.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current sessions list against the last known state.\n\nLast known state (from heartbeat-state.json):\n- Active sessions: 5 — cron:ed2d0b5d, cron:6f3323ef, cron:e7885813, cron:ac986a8d, telegram:group:-5163901258\n- Pipeline: HEALTHY\n- Blocker: Telegram gateway timeout\n\nCurrent sessions (from sessions_list, excluding this cron session and old/ended sessions):\n\nRunning sessions:\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — status: running (startedAt: 1776161997437) — THIS IS THIS SESSION\n\n\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — status: running (startedAt: 1776152701090) — ~2h 10m ago\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` — status: running (startedAt: 1776143077282) — ~2h 19m ago\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — status: running (startedAt: 1776161006770)\n\nSo the main session ended and got replaced by this new cron job at 10:19, while most other sessions are still running from earlier today.\n\nI'm noticing the cron:e7885813 session that ran the Agent Status to Lead job at 10:02 UTC is still showing as active, which is odd since it only takes about 20 seconds to complete.\n\nLooking at the cron:ac986a8d session, it also appears to be a brief task that should've finished quickly rather than running for 1.5 hours. The real issue here is that my presence state file doesn't actually exist at that path—the cron is still referencing it, but the state file is missing.\n\nSo the sessions that matter are the three still actively running: the main cron (ed2d0b5d) which is this session itself, the DTLX 5p cron (6f3323ef) that's been going for about 2 hours, and the Telegram group session (telegram:group:-5163901258) that's been running for 2 hours 15 minutes.\n\nNow I'm checking for actual changes since the last report at 10:09 UTC. The sessions that were transient—e7885813 and ac986a8d—both ended after sending their reports, and the Telegram group session is still running. The Telegram delivery blocker persists but was already documented, so there's no new status to report.\n\nLooking at the lead direct session more carefully: it failed at 07:04 UTC but then restarted and is now running again since 10:04 UTC. That's actually a significant state change—the session recovered. I need to verify whether this was already captured in the 10:09 report before deciding if this warrants a new update.\n\nNow checking for other session changes: the cron:e7885813 session that was running at 10:09 has since ended, which is a new termination worth noting.\n\nLooking at the full picture, I see three key changes since the last report — the Lead direct session recovered, the Agent Status cron ended after sending its report, and the Telegram delivery cron also ended. The Telegram gateway timeout blocker persists as it was, so I'm ready to compile this into a report. I'm realizing the Telegram delivery cron is probably a re-trigger of the original one that keeps retrying the failed message, so it's still active but stuck. Let me finalize my report with the key changes: the Lead direct session is back up after the morning failure, the two notification crons have both completed their runs, and the Telegram blocker remains the same as before.","thinkingSignature":"940ad66d7234209f35ead22df65c9c6417a4490516157131eaa29988c446117d"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Comparing current state vs. last known state (10:09 UTC):\n\n**Last known (10:09 UTC):**\n- 5 sessions: ed2d0b5d, 6f3323ef, e7885813, ac986a8d, telegram:group:-5163901258\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 — FAILED (hadn't restarted yet)\n\n**Current (10:19 UTC):**\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 — now **running** (restarted at ~10:04 UTC, was already noted in last DTLX